1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:00:30,762 --> 00:00:33,026
<i>[Man Panting]</i>

3
00:01:35,193 --> 00:01:40,460
Ca Lu, half a click that way,
two-nine-zero.

4
00:01:40,532 --> 00:01:42,898
- I say we go right up the middle.
- Negative.

5
00:01:42,968 --> 00:01:45,994
One round flank up the hill, the
other one right through the swamp.

6
00:01:48,740 --> 00:01:51,732
Heads, you get the hill.
Tails, you get the swamp.

7
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:53,744
Flip the motherfucker.

8
00:01:55,714 --> 00:01:57,978
- See you in Ca Lu.
- All right.

9
00:02:35,053 --> 00:02:36,987
[Mouths Words]

10
00:03:10,488 --> 00:03:12,422
<i>[Man Speaking</i>
<i>In Vietnamese]</i>

11
00:03:19,864 --> 00:03:21,798
[Vietnamese]

12
00:03:47,092 --> 00:03:49,026
<i>[Vietnamese Continues]</i>

13
00:04:23,028 --> 00:04:25,189
[Shouting]

14
00:04:29,834 --> 00:04:32,268
Delta Two, whats your SITREP?
Over.

15
00:04:32,337 --> 00:04:34,430
What do you got,
Gibson?

16
00:04:34,506 --> 00:04:38,704
Nothing, sir.
Delta One, Delta Two, SITREP. Over.

17
00:04:38,777 --> 00:04:41,041
Two-one, contact!
Contact way out!

18
00:04:49,621 --> 00:04:51,555
[Screams]

19
00:04:51,623 --> 00:04:55,684
Cease fire! Cease fire!

20
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:59,127
<i>Go, go, go.</i>
<i>Lets get 'em!</i>

21
00:04:59,197 --> 00:05:01,131
Come outta there!

22
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:03,531
Put your hands on your head!
Get on your knees now!

23
00:05:03,601 --> 00:05:05,660
Come on!
Down, down.

24
00:05:05,737 --> 00:05:08,365
Come on out of there!
Now!

25
00:05:10,709 --> 00:05:15,703
<i>How many you slopes are out here?</i>
<i>Huh? Whats your unit? Whats in it?</i>

26
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:18,715
Tuan, get over here!
Talk to these motherfuckers!

27
00:05:18,783 --> 00:05:21,581
- Find out how many of them are here!
- [Translating In Vietnamese]

28
00:05:21,653 --> 00:05:25,180
<i>Where are they? Whats in it?</i>
<i>Talk to me, goddamn it!</i>

29
00:05:25,256 --> 00:05:27,247
<i>[Tuan Continues]</i>

30
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:37,726
Aah!

31
00:05:53,118 --> 00:05:56,087
Two, this is One Actual.
Where are you?

32
00:06:01,159 --> 00:06:03,855
[Gunfire On Radio]

33
00:06:04,763 --> 00:06:06,697
Uuh!

34
00:06:17,809 --> 00:06:21,142
Other side of the tree line.
I'm in the water unable to withdraw.

35
00:06:22,781 --> 00:06:28,242
Unable to withdraw! I'm calling
in a fire mission on this position!

36
00:06:31,356 --> 00:06:34,655
- Hurry up and drop that arty!
- They're all over!

37
00:06:34,726 --> 00:06:37,160
[Static,
Transmission Crackling]

38
00:06:37,228 --> 00:06:39,321
[Man]
Go left! Get out there!

39
00:06:39,397 --> 00:06:42,628
Tell this man to get on that radio
and pull his men off Hodges.

40
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:45,168
Tell him to break contact
and move his men north of Ca Lu!

41
00:06:45,236 --> 00:06:47,932
[Translating]

42
00:06:48,006 --> 00:06:51,498
Tell him I ain't playin'!
Pull his men off Hodges now!

43
00:06:51,576 --> 00:06:53,840
<i>[Tuan Continues]</i>

44
00:06:53,912 --> 00:06:56,005
I ain't bullshittin'
with you.

45
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,014
Either you call your men off
Hodges,

46
00:06:58,082 --> 00:07:00,744
or this motherfucker's
dead and you're next.

47
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:04,186
- <i>[Tuan Continues]</i>
- <i>Last warnin'!</i>

48
00:07:08,193 --> 00:07:10,753
Uuh!

49
00:07:10,829 --> 00:07:14,287
Call your men
off Hodges now!

50
00:07:14,365 --> 00:07:18,802
If he does, he can go.
He's got my word on that.

51
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:22,966
If you don't,
I'll kill you where you stand.

52
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:24,975
<i>[Tuan Continues]</i>

53
00:07:30,915 --> 00:07:32,849
[Groaning]

54
00:07:46,831 --> 00:07:48,765
[Vietnamese]

55
00:07:49,868 --> 00:07:51,802
[Men Shouting]

56
00:07:57,141 --> 00:07:59,075
[Groaning]

57
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:22,297
<i>[Man On Radio] Two, this is</i>
<i>One Actual. You still with me?</i>

58
00:08:28,773 --> 00:08:31,833
Crank off a pop-up
if you're still alive.

59
00:08:33,311 --> 00:08:35,245
[Grunts]

60
00:08:45,356 --> 00:08:49,725
You got a reprieve, you hear me?
You don't get to die today.

61
00:08:49,794 --> 00:08:52,160
<i>You got your "Hail Mary."</i>

62
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:38,074
<i>?? [Blues Rock]</i>

63
00:09:42,347 --> 00:09:47,614
<i>Hey! Its the colonel</i>
<i>with his cover on!</i>

64
00:09:47,685 --> 00:09:49,619
<i>[Cheering, Applause]</i>

65
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,932
All right!
Make way, make way!

66
00:10:05,003 --> 00:10:08,530
- I guess the drinks are on me.
- All right!

67
00:10:08,606 --> 00:10:10,540
At ease!
Listen up.

68
00:10:12,310 --> 00:10:16,110
- <i>?? [Stops]</i>
- Ladies and gentlemen,

69
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:20,844
<i>the reason we're all here,</i>
<i>Colonel Hayes Hodges.</i>

70
00:10:20,918 --> 00:10:22,852
[Cheering]

71
00:10:31,029 --> 00:10:36,331
He's calling it a career after
32 years of distinguished service.

72
00:10:40,071 --> 00:10:42,005
All right, all right.

73
00:10:43,141 --> 00:10:45,974
Colonel, we got you a gift
and a surprise,

74
00:10:46,044 --> 00:10:48,478
so don't act like
you're not coming up here.

75
00:10:48,546 --> 00:10:50,980
[All Chanting]
Speech! Speech! Speech!

76
00:10:55,553 --> 00:10:57,544
Speech! Speech!
Speech!

77
00:11:01,059 --> 00:11:02,924
<i>[Cheering]</i>

78
00:11:05,930 --> 00:11:07,864
Hey, my man!

79
00:11:14,872 --> 00:11:16,806
Good to see you.

80
00:11:16,874 --> 00:11:20,401
You damn well better be. I came
halfway 'round the world for this.

81
00:11:30,021 --> 00:11:31,955
Hey, get up here.

82
00:11:36,928 --> 00:11:38,862
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Speech!</i>

83
00:11:40,865 --> 00:11:44,232
The sword, Colonel.
You know the story, Hayes.

84
00:11:44,302 --> 00:11:47,100
Marine Lieutenant Presley O'Banion
defeated the Barbary pirates...

85
00:11:47,171 --> 00:11:49,401
on the shores of Tripoli
in 1805.

86
00:11:49,474 --> 00:11:52,568
Out of gratitude, the pasha
gave him the Mameluke sword.

87
00:11:52,643 --> 00:11:55,134
Marine officers have
carried one ever since.

88
00:11:55,213 --> 00:11:57,545
Its the symbol
of a warrior,

89
00:11:57,615 --> 00:12:00,550
and you are a warrior.

90
00:12:00,618 --> 00:12:04,213
- <i>[Cheering]</i>
- The best I ever served with.

91
00:12:08,626 --> 00:12:11,060
This man's been riding a desk
for the past 28 years,

92
00:12:11,129 --> 00:12:13,620
but not because he wanted to.

93
00:12:13,698 --> 00:12:16,462
He knows how to fight.
Its in his blood. Ah-ooh!

94
00:12:20,872 --> 00:12:23,602
<i>[Man] What are you</i>
<i>gonna do now, Colonel?</i>

95
00:12:23,674 --> 00:12:26,609
Well, uh... Well.

96
00:12:26,677 --> 00:12:29,703
Heh! No more wars to fight,
no more trials to lose.

97
00:12:29,780 --> 00:12:31,714
- [Clears Throat]
- <i>[Laughter]</i>

98
00:12:31,782 --> 00:12:34,876
So I expect I'll do
some teaching at V.M.I.

99
00:12:34,952 --> 00:12:38,012
I will recon the local restaurants
in a concerted effort...

100
00:12:38,089 --> 00:12:41,889
- to find out what civilians eat.
- <i>[Laughter]</i>

101
00:12:41,959 --> 00:12:45,019
Of course, I intend to continue
serving my country...

102
00:12:45,096 --> 00:12:47,257
by honorably depleting
the trout streams...

103
00:12:47,331 --> 00:12:50,266
of the Southern United States
with my fly rod!

104
00:12:53,171 --> 00:12:55,105
Thats about it.

105
00:12:59,043 --> 00:13:00,977
Lets get outta here.

106
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:08,981
- I missed you.
- Yeah, I missed you too.

107
00:13:09,053 --> 00:13:11,317
How's the kid,
the smart Hodges?

108
00:13:11,389 --> 00:13:15,519
You know, he studies more than
any two people. I never see him.

109
00:13:15,593 --> 00:13:18,790
- You gotta fix that.
- Yeah.

110
00:13:20,965 --> 00:13:23,331
- Got my orders.
- Oh, yeah? What?

111
00:13:23,401 --> 00:13:26,768
Got command of the 24th
Marine Expeditionary Unit.

112
00:13:26,837 --> 00:13:30,967
- Special Operations capable.
- Congrats. Huh! Congrats.

113
00:13:31,042 --> 00:13:32,976
- Yeah.
- Outstanding.

114
00:13:33,044 --> 00:13:35,740
All I gotta do is lash
'em together, take 'em to sea.

115
00:13:37,248 --> 00:13:39,443
[Quietly]
Thats, uh... outstanding.

116
00:13:41,852 --> 00:13:45,686
You ain't missin' nothin', Hodge.
Its a whole new ball game.

117
00:13:45,756 --> 00:13:48,748
No friends, no enemies,
no front, no rear.

118
00:13:48,826 --> 00:13:51,090
No victories, no defeats,
no Mama, no Papa.

119
00:13:51,162 --> 00:13:54,256
- Yeah.
- We're orphans out there.

120
00:13:54,332 --> 00:13:56,562
Its funny, you know?

121
00:13:56,634 --> 00:13:59,228
One guy walks out through a swamp,
he gets to come home to a desk.

122
00:13:59,303 --> 00:14:01,669
Another guy drives up a hill
and he gets to still be doin' it,

123
00:14:01,739 --> 00:14:03,764
all over the flip
of a goddamn coin.

124
00:14:03,841 --> 00:14:05,775
You know, thats...

125
00:14:08,212 --> 00:14:11,181
Its funny.

126
00:14:11,249 --> 00:14:14,616
You gave good service
to the corps, Hodge.

127
00:14:14,685 --> 00:14:18,621
To think otherwise
would be just plain crazy.

128
00:14:18,689 --> 00:14:21,783
- You'd have gotten your command.
- Oh, yeah, sure.

129
00:14:24,128 --> 00:14:25,959
[Sighs]

130
00:14:45,283 --> 00:14:47,649
<i>[Man On P.A.,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

131
00:14:54,959 --> 00:14:56,893
Whats up, John?

132
00:14:56,961 --> 00:15:00,397
Terry, we've been ordered
to the Arabian Sea, Gulf of Aden.

133
00:15:00,464 --> 00:15:03,160
This comes straight down Second
Division through General Perry.

134
00:15:03,234 --> 00:15:05,168
The American Embassy in Yemen
is surrounded...

135
00:15:05,236 --> 00:15:06,703
by a crowd of demonstrators.

136
00:15:06,771 --> 00:15:08,204
The crowd isn't hostile,
but its large enough...

137
00:15:08,272 --> 00:15:11,435
to spook their government
into pulling their security forces.

138
00:15:11,509 --> 00:15:14,808
Twenty-fourth Marine Expeditionary
Units gonna provide extra security.

139
00:15:14,879 --> 00:15:17,814
We're gonna baby-sit, Colonel.
Just show our presence.

140
00:15:17,882 --> 00:15:20,646
Remember, though, if it turns
hot, we're looking at an evac.

141
00:15:20,718 --> 00:15:24,051
We got an ambassador and his family
there. Let me run you through this.

142
00:15:24,121 --> 00:15:26,055
Here's your
potential L.Z.s.

143
00:15:26,123 --> 00:15:29,183
Marines at the embassy advise we can
gain entrance through the back way.

144
00:15:29,260 --> 00:15:31,854
Here's some stairs where you
can deploy your men to the roof.

145
00:15:31,929 --> 00:15:34,022
These are your
over-watch positions.

146
00:15:34,098 --> 00:15:36,293
I'll take them in
myself quietly.

147
00:15:36,367 --> 00:15:39,700
One platoon, TRAP team,
put everyone else on Ready Five.

148
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:41,761
My thoughts exactly,
Colonel.

149
00:15:44,942 --> 00:15:47,775
[Indistinct Shouts]

150
00:16:24,081 --> 00:16:26,515
[Chanting In
Native Language]

151
00:16:45,469 --> 00:16:47,699
<i>[Chanting Continues]</i>

152
00:17:07,091 --> 00:17:09,423
[Boy]
Whats wrong, Mommy?

153
00:17:09,493 --> 00:17:11,927
The people are upset
about some things, darling.

154
00:17:11,996 --> 00:17:15,022
- Are they mad at Daddy?
- No, they're not mad at your daddy.

155
00:17:15,099 --> 00:17:17,033
Why are they yelling?

156
00:17:17,101 --> 00:17:21,435
They're trying to get attention
so that people will listen to them.

157
00:17:50,901 --> 00:17:53,802
Sir, state security analysts
are asking for an assessment.

158
00:17:53,871 --> 00:17:56,806
Assessment? We're getting the hell
out of here. Thats the assessment.

159
00:17:56,874 --> 00:17:59,342
The Sixth Fleet marines
are in the air, sir.

160
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:01,935
If they think I'm gonna
tough this one out, they're crazy.

161
00:18:02,012 --> 00:18:04,776
Tell Mrs. Mourain to start packing.
We're going home.

162
00:18:04,849 --> 00:18:07,079
Shall I indicate
we're ready to evacuate?

163
00:18:07,151 --> 00:18:09,449
Ask them where the hell
are those helicopters!

164
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,351
The ambassador wants to know
where the choppers are.

165
00:18:11,422 --> 00:18:13,583
You heard me.
Where the hell are the choppers?

166
00:18:20,064 --> 00:18:23,329
<i>[Indistinct</i>
<i>Radio Transmission]</i>

167
00:18:37,748 --> 00:18:39,682
[Shouting]

168
00:19:14,885 --> 00:19:17,046
Lock and load!
Lock and load!

169
00:19:17,121 --> 00:19:19,453
Lock and load!
Lock and load!

170
00:19:53,657 --> 00:19:55,625
<i>[Bullets Ricochetting]</i>

171
00:20:26,924 --> 00:20:30,655
<i>[Man On Radio] We're gonna</i>
<i>take a better look before we go in.</i>

172
00:20:30,728 --> 00:20:33,561
[Grunting, Groaning]

173
00:20:44,642 --> 00:20:48,442
Wagon Wheel, this is Red Man.
I'm over the embassy.

174
00:20:48,512 --> 00:20:51,413
<i>This ain't no baby-sit.</i>
<i>Its ugly down there.</i>

175
00:20:51,482 --> 00:20:53,416
<i>[Man On Radio]</i>
<i>Red Man, Wagon Wheel.</i>

176
00:20:53,484 --> 00:20:55,349
<i>Roger that.</i>
<i>Lets go for the evac.</i>

177
00:20:55,419 --> 00:20:58,479
Put it on deck.
We're going in the north side.

178
00:21:26,350 --> 00:21:29,217
[Indistinct Shouts]

179
00:22:00,718 --> 00:22:03,983
There! Go!

180
00:22:06,623 --> 00:22:08,557
- Captain Lee!
- <i>[Lee] Yes, sir!</i>

181
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:11,753
Nobody comes over those walls
or through those gates. Nobody!

182
00:22:11,829 --> 00:22:15,595
One Alpha, secure all entries.
Tango and Bravo, on the walls!

183
00:22:15,666 --> 00:22:19,693
- Move, move, move!
- Last man! Last man!

184
00:22:21,271 --> 00:22:24,604
Pull back! Pull back!
[Indistinct]

185
00:22:30,414 --> 00:22:32,439
Take cover!

186
00:22:37,955 --> 00:22:41,083
- [Childers] You speak English?
- Yes!

187
00:22:41,158 --> 00:22:44,719
Where's the ambassador?
He's topside! Go topside!

188
00:22:49,767 --> 00:22:53,897
[Man] Take that corner!
Take that side! Move!

189
00:23:00,544 --> 00:23:02,409
Aah!

190
00:23:03,514 --> 00:23:05,982
Move, move, move!
Go, go!

191
00:23:07,551 --> 00:23:09,883
Bravo Two, left!
Move, move, move!

192
00:23:09,953 --> 00:23:12,820
Incoming sniper fire!
Stay down! Stay down!

193
00:23:15,793 --> 00:23:18,023
- Two blue, clear!
- [Mrs. Mourain Yelps]

194
00:23:18,095 --> 00:23:21,064
- Who's Mrs. Mourain?
- L-I'm Mrs. Mourain.

195
00:23:21,131 --> 00:23:24,396
- Where's the ambassador?
- He's in there. Are we leaving?

196
00:23:24,468 --> 00:23:27,062
The helos are outside, ma'am,
but thats up to the ambassador.

197
00:23:27,137 --> 00:23:29,401
Stay away from
the windows, please.

198
00:23:30,974 --> 00:23:32,908
Duck! Ow!

199
00:23:32,976 --> 00:23:36,070
Aah! Colonel! Please!

200
00:23:38,248 --> 00:23:41,775
My God! Are the helicopters here?
What kept you people so long?

201
00:23:41,852 --> 00:23:44,946
We're ready to evacuate, unless you
want to stay and run the embassy.

202
00:23:45,022 --> 00:23:48,116
I want to go right... now!
We called hours ago!

203
00:23:48,192 --> 00:23:51,286
All right, sir, come to me.
Stay calm and come to me.

204
00:23:51,361 --> 00:23:56,822
<i>- Stay calm. Come to me. Stay low.</i>
- We're like targets!

205
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:59,494
- We're sitting targets!
- Follow Sergeant Mac. Go!

206
00:24:05,008 --> 00:24:08,273
Come on! Down there!
Down there! Right there!

207
00:24:12,950 --> 00:24:15,646
Right there!
Down there! Down there!

208
00:24:38,575 --> 00:24:40,566
Go ahead, ma'am!

209
00:24:40,644 --> 00:24:43,545
Go ahead!
Go ahead, ma'am, go ahead!

210
00:24:43,614 --> 00:24:47,311
<i>Come on, son. Come on!</i>

211
00:24:47,384 --> 00:24:49,682
- Whats your name, son? Justin?
- Justin.

212
00:24:49,753 --> 00:24:52,551
[Sobbing]
Come on, Justin! Come on!

213
00:24:52,623 --> 00:24:55,148
- Justin, whats that you got there?
- A flashlight.

214
00:24:55,225 --> 00:24:58,023
We're gonna ride in a helicopter.
Wanna bring that with you?

215
00:24:58,095 --> 00:25:01,861
- Huh? Come on. Come on!
- Mommy!

216
00:25:01,932 --> 00:25:04,662
Lets go, ma'am, go!
Go, go, go!

217
00:25:08,872 --> 00:25:11,636
All TRAP Unit six,
stay low, stay low!

218
00:25:11,708 --> 00:25:14,700
We got crap coming over the walls
and sniper fire at 100 meters. Over.

219
00:25:14,778 --> 00:25:18,179
Stay low! Sit tight,
sit tight, sit tight!

220
00:25:18,248 --> 00:25:20,716
[Continues, Indistinct]

221
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:32,895
Colonel, we got three marines hit!
One is K.I.A.

222
00:25:32,963 --> 00:25:35,557
One Alpha says they're gonna
try to breach the front gate!

223
00:25:35,632 --> 00:25:37,896
- Tell them to wait out!
- Roger that!

224
00:25:37,968 --> 00:25:40,766
- [Indistinct Shouts]
- <i>[Helicopter Blades Whirring]</i>

225
00:25:46,076 --> 00:25:51,810
<i>[Man] Put the missus on board</i>
<i>first. Get in there, Mr. Ambassador.</i>

226
00:25:51,882 --> 00:25:55,147
I'll personally recommend you...
Where's the belt?

227
00:25:55,218 --> 00:25:58,654
- I'll personally recommend...
- Hold it!

228
00:25:58,722 --> 00:26:03,716
<i>Where are you going? What? Colonel!</i>
