This is a tape from
the embassy security system.

283
00:31:39,696 --> 00:31:42,187
- Want me to thread it up?
- No. I don't want to watch videos.

284
00:31:42,265 --> 00:31:44,631
I don't want to hear about
ammo casings in some building,

285
00:31:44,701 --> 00:31:48,137
'cause here I got
83 dead people...

286
00:31:48,204 --> 00:31:51,071
unarmed...
women, children, old men.

287
00:31:51,141 --> 00:31:53,268
Another hundred or so
critically wounded.

288
00:31:53,343 --> 00:31:57,746
Here I got an international
crisis of mega fucking proportions!

289
00:31:57,814 --> 00:31:59,748
Bill, you know there have been
regular reports...

290
00:31:59,816 --> 00:32:02,011
of a terrorist
plot against this embassy.

291
00:32:02,085 --> 00:32:05,418
This was a regularly scheduled
protest. It was every week.

292
00:32:05,488 --> 00:32:08,855
It was the usual bullshit about
American presence in the gulf.

293
00:32:08,925 --> 00:32:12,884
Have you looked at these?
I mean, I'm just assuming you have,

294
00:32:12,962 --> 00:32:16,762
since they're on the front page
of every newspaper in the world.

295
00:32:16,833 --> 00:32:19,631
Its not that the rest of the
world <i>wants</i> to hold us responsible,

296
00:32:19,703 --> 00:32:21,637
we <i>are</i> responsible!

297
00:32:23,606 --> 00:32:26,370
We can't even have
the appearance of a cover-up.

298
00:32:26,443 --> 00:32:29,469
That does not excuse us
from our duty, Mr. Sokal.

299
00:32:29,546 --> 00:32:34,506
We sent Colonel Childers in there,
and the mission went to shit.

300
00:32:34,584 --> 00:32:37,075
We can't go after the man
who carried out his orders...

301
00:32:37,153 --> 00:32:39,519
and ignore the people
who issued those orders.

302
00:32:39,589 --> 00:32:41,523
Childers ordered the slaughter...

303
00:32:41,591 --> 00:32:43,923
of innocent women and children.
Get that straight right now.

304
00:32:43,993 --> 00:32:45,358
I'll tell you
what we ought to get straight.

305
00:32:45,428 --> 00:32:47,225
We lost three
United States Marines.

306
00:32:47,297 --> 00:32:49,993
They lost 83!

307
00:32:50,066 --> 00:32:53,092
Now, are we gonna go to war
with Yemen over it?

308
00:32:53,169 --> 00:32:56,935
We're covering our ass all over
the Middle East right now, General.

309
00:32:57,006 --> 00:32:59,566
Because of your man's
hotheaded miscalculation,

310
00:32:59,642 --> 00:33:03,908
we are in danger of losing embassies
in Saudi, Jordan and Egypt.

311
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:06,676
We're in danger
of losing our presence...

312
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:09,583
with every moderate
in the region.

313
00:33:09,652 --> 00:33:11,950
Now they're gonna scream
"cover up."

314
00:33:12,021 --> 00:33:15,252
The screaming will get so loud we'll
be sending Marines back over there,

315
00:33:15,325 --> 00:33:18,726
and the body count of American
dead is gonna be higher than three.

316
00:33:20,563 --> 00:33:24,226
I see where you're going
with this, Mr. Sokal.

317
00:33:24,300 --> 00:33:26,564
Will you be needing me
anymore today?

318
00:33:27,971 --> 00:33:29,996
No.

319
00:33:30,073 --> 00:33:32,405
No, thats fine, General.
Thank you.

320
00:33:32,475 --> 00:33:34,568
Good day to you, sir.

321
00:33:47,791 --> 00:33:51,158
[Sighs] Where do you think
you're going with that?

322
00:33:51,227 --> 00:33:56,221
- You don't want to look at it.
- Nobody's lookin' at it.

323
00:33:56,299 --> 00:33:58,733
Why should the United States
be held responsible...

324
00:33:58,802 --> 00:34:02,670
for the actions of one man?

325
00:34:02,739 --> 00:34:05,105
What if the crowd
had weapons?

326
00:34:05,175 --> 00:34:07,700
What if this shows
they did fire first?

327
00:34:07,777 --> 00:34:10,905
He could have fired over
their heads, this moron!

328
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:13,608
Didn't he know where he was?
The Middle East!

329
00:34:13,683 --> 00:34:15,378
He could have isolated
on the snipers.

330
00:34:15,452 --> 00:34:16,942
He could have
avoided confrontation.

331
00:34:17,020 --> 00:34:19,352
He could have done
50 fuckin' things!

332
00:34:19,422 --> 00:34:21,720
Instead, he destroyed a fragile
trust, put his own men in danger...

333
00:34:21,791 --> 00:34:25,283
Fuck this guy!
Forget this tape.

334
00:34:25,361 --> 00:34:29,297
I don't want to watch it.
I don't want to testify about it.

335
00:34:31,668 --> 00:34:33,636
I don't want it to exist.

336
00:34:34,790 --> 00:34:36,724
<i>[Men Shouting In Distance,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

337
00:34:45,801 --> 00:34:47,894
[Women Together]
Good morning, sir.

338
00:34:49,104 --> 00:34:51,038
[Together]
Good morning, sir.

339
00:34:53,842 --> 00:34:55,776
Aye, aye, sir.

340
00:34:55,844 --> 00:34:59,280
- <i>[Man, Indistinct]</i>
- <i>[General] As soon as its time.</i>

341
00:35:02,918 --> 00:35:06,718
General, Colonel Childers
reporting as ordered, sir.

342
00:35:06,788 --> 00:35:08,881
- Give us a minute, Skip.
- Yes, sir.

343
00:35:13,262 --> 00:35:18,222
Colonel, its my duty to inform
you that you've been charged with...

344
00:35:20,135 --> 00:35:24,094
[Sighs]
You know the drill.

345
00:35:27,643 --> 00:35:29,577
This is the Article 32
investigation.

346
00:35:29,645 --> 00:35:31,704
You're facing
a general court-martial...

347
00:35:31,780 --> 00:35:34,578
and charged with violation
of at least three articles...

348
00:35:34,650 --> 00:35:37,210
everything from "breach of peace"
to "conduct unbecoming."

349
00:35:37,286 --> 00:35:43,156
But the bottom line... 83 counts,
violation of Article 118, murder.

350
00:35:43,225 --> 00:35:45,159
You issued an illegal order
to have your marines...

351
00:35:45,227 --> 00:35:48,458
fire into a group
of innocent civilians.

352
00:35:48,530 --> 00:35:50,930
Murder, sir?

353
00:35:54,903 --> 00:35:58,566
I'm the convening authority, so I've
gotta get this B.S. Out of the way.

354
00:36:01,176 --> 00:36:03,974
Sign here, initial here.

355
00:36:07,883 --> 00:36:12,445
You're not a flight risk, so there
won't be any pretrial confinement.

356
00:36:16,525 --> 00:36:18,959
This court-martial convenes
in eight days...

357
00:36:19,027 --> 00:36:24,021
by direct order of
the national command authority.

358
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:27,466
<i>Do you want me to call</i>
<i>Bob Bennett or one of those guys,</i>

359
00:36:27,536 --> 00:36:29,970
or do you want to go
with base legal?

360
00:36:32,541 --> 00:36:36,978
<i>Terry, goddamn it,</i>
<i>we've been friends for 20 years.</i>

361
00:36:40,816 --> 00:36:43,979
You want to tell me exactly
what the hell happened out there?

362
00:36:46,021 --> 00:36:50,788
I lost marines. The crowd
was hostile. They fired on us.

363
00:36:50,859 --> 00:36:54,317
They fired first, sir.

364
00:36:54,396 --> 00:36:57,331
I want you to know
I did everything in the world...

365
00:36:57,399 --> 00:36:59,196
to keep this from happening.

366
00:36:59,267 --> 00:37:01,997
Its just out
of my hands now.

367
00:37:13,982 --> 00:37:15,916
Thanks a lot.

368
00:37:15,984 --> 00:37:18,612
When's the last time you
actually caught something here?

369
00:37:19,955 --> 00:37:22,753
- Two years.
- <i>[Chuckles]</i>

370
00:37:27,496 --> 00:37:30,761
- I really need your help.
- I'll help. Anything you need.

371
00:37:30,832 --> 00:37:33,164
You want me to take the stand?
I'll be a character witness.

372
00:37:33,235 --> 00:37:35,499
No, you don't understand
what I'm asking.

373
00:37:36,571 --> 00:37:39,563
I want you
to be my lawyer.

374
00:37:39,641 --> 00:37:41,575
[Sighs]

375
00:37:43,478 --> 00:37:47,039
I'm a good enough lawyer to know
you need a better lawyer than me.

376
00:37:47,115 --> 00:37:49,049
'Sides that, I'm short.

377
00:37:49,117 --> 00:37:50,550
Two-nine plus one wake-up,
and I'm gone.

378
00:37:50,619 --> 00:37:52,712
You need one of those
Washington cats.

379
00:37:52,788 --> 00:37:56,918
I don't want some Starbucks
drinker who's never seen combat.

380
00:37:56,992 --> 00:38:00,223
- I need somebody who's been shot at.
- Yeah, I've been shot at.

381
00:38:00,295 --> 00:38:03,458
Thats what I am...
a shot-up marine.

382
00:38:03,532 --> 00:38:07,161
As a matter of fact,
thats all the hell I am.

383
00:38:07,235 --> 00:38:09,897
No, wait a minute.
I'm also a weak lawyer.

384
00:38:10,972 --> 00:38:14,066
I'm a very weak lawyer...

385
00:38:14,142 --> 00:38:18,806
and the government is gonna come
at you with everything they've got.

386
00:38:28,089 --> 00:38:31,149
Major, Bill Sokal. Its a pleasure
to meet you. Come on in.

387
00:38:31,226 --> 00:38:33,160
Let me introduce you.

388
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:35,162
Gentlemen, this
is Major Mark Biggs.

389
00:38:35,230 --> 00:38:37,357
He'll be prosecuting
the Childers court-martial.

390
00:38:37,432 --> 00:38:39,866
The marines put the major
through Stanford Law,

391
00:38:39,935 --> 00:38:43,371
and he owes them a couple of years
before he takes over the world.

392
00:38:43,438 --> 00:38:45,372
<i>You know General Lowry.</i>

393
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,533
<i>I'd like you to meet the general</i>
<i>of theJoint Chiefs of Staff,</i>

394
00:38:47,609 --> 00:38:50,476
General West, and the secretary
of Defense, Mr. Wyatt.

395
00:38:50,545 --> 00:38:52,479
Have a seat.
Make yourself comfortable.

396
00:38:52,547 --> 00:38:56,347
What I gather from our esteemed NSC
advisor and secretary of state...

397
00:38:56,418 --> 00:38:58,613
is that we've got a trial
in two weeks.

398
00:38:58,687 --> 00:39:01,986
- Seems awfully damned fast.
- Everyone in this room will agree...

399
00:39:02,057 --> 00:39:04,787
its in the national interest that
this trial be moved along quickly.

400
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:08,660
The Article 32 investigation
was complete and comprehensive.

401
00:39:08,730 --> 00:39:10,459
It all seems to point
in one direction.

402
00:39:10,532 --> 00:39:11,897
Has he got a lawyer yet?

403
00:39:11,967 --> 00:39:14,902
He's requested a military
attorney, Colonel Hayes Hodges.

404
00:39:14,970 --> 00:39:17,700
Second Marine Division, Lejeune.

405
00:39:17,772 --> 00:39:19,467
Any relation to
General H. Lawrence Hodges?

406
00:39:19,541 --> 00:39:20,667
His son.

407
00:39:20,742 --> 00:39:23,404
Larry Hodges was one of this country's
most distinguished officers.

408
00:39:23,478 --> 00:39:25,639
What do we know about
Colonel Hayes Hodges?

409
00:39:25,714 --> 00:39:28,148
He's a guy who got
blown apart in Vietnam,

410
00:39:28,216 --> 00:39:30,912
then went to Georgetown Law
and became a cynic.

411
00:39:30,986 --> 00:39:32,920
Is that about right, Major?

412
00:39:32,988 --> 00:39:35,081
He was 67th in his class
at Georgetown, sir.

413
00:39:35,156 --> 00:39:38,023
He doesn't take too many cases,
doesn't win too many.

414
00:39:38,093 --> 00:39:40,857
He apparently went through an ugly
divorce, had a drinking problem,

415
00:39:40,929 --> 00:39:45,491
- <i>retiring in two weeks.</i>
- Can we guarantee we get this guy?

416
00:39:45,567 --> 00:39:48,092
Sir, if I may
say something?

417
00:39:49,237 --> 00:39:51,330
I am not a hired gun.

418
00:39:51,406 --> 00:39:52,839
I accepted this assignment...

419
00:39:52,908 --> 00:39:55,274
'cause I believe in the merits
of the governments case.

420
00:39:55,343 --> 00:39:57,538
I am not gonna stack the deck
against this guy.

421
00:39:57,612 --> 00:40:00,445
I will try this case
on good evidence only.

422
00:40:00,515 --> 00:40:02,847
I'm glad to hear it.

423
00:40:37,085 --> 00:40:40,077
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Hold your fire.</i>

424
00:40:40,155 --> 00:40:43,386
<i>- Set that weapon down over here.</i>
- <i>[Man, Indistinct]</i>

425
00:40:46,561 --> 00:40:50,327
<i>[Man, Distant] We need</i>
<i>a couple of canteens up here.</i>

426
00:40:50,398 --> 00:40:52,332
<i>[Helicopter Blades</i>
<i>Whirring]</i>

427
00:40:56,404 --> 00:40:58,998
<i>- [Man] Party incoming!</i>
- You can go.

428
00:40:59,074 --> 00:41:02,100
You can go, goddamn it!
Go on! Dee dee!

429
00:41:02,177 --> 00:41:05,613
Get the fuck out of here
before I change my mind!

430
00:41:10,452 --> 00:41:13,080
<i>Looks like you're going back</i>
<i>to the world, baby.</i>

431
00:41:13,154 --> 00:41:17,352
- Doc!
<i>- [Man] Twenty meters out. Left!</i>

432
00:41:17,425 --> 00:41:20,758
- <i>Right there.</i>
- <i>[Hodges] Anybody else?</i>

433
00:41:37,846 --> 00:41:39,780
[Child Giggles]

434
00:41:41,149 --> 00:41:43,083
I got you now!

435
00:41:44,686 --> 00:41:46,620
- Hey, buddy!
- Hi, Mom.

436
00:41:48,690 --> 00:41:50,624
He looks fabulous.

437
00:41:50,692 --> 00:41:52,557
- Happy anniversary, Mom.
- Oh, thank you. So good to see you.

438
00:41:52,627 --> 00:41:54,060
I wasn't sure you'd make it.

439
00:41:54,129 --> 00:41:56,097
- You look wonderful.
- Thank you.

440
00:41:56,164 --> 00:41:58,724
- How's it feel to be retired?
- Um, crazy.

441
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,392
Good. Oh, you look great.

442
00:42:00,468 --> 00:42:01,833
- Thank you.
- Well, come see Dad...

443
00:42:01,903 --> 00:42:04,167
- There he is.
- And all the family.

444
00:42:04,239 --> 00:42:06,730
Hello, sir.

445
00:42:06,808 --> 00:42:09,242
- Glad you could make it.
- Yes, sir.

446
00:42:09,310 --> 00:42:11,244
<i>[Laughter,</i>
<i>Crowd Chatter]</i>

447
00:42:14,949 --> 00:42:18,180
- [Man] Good to see you, Hayes.
- How are you doing?

448
00:42:18,253 --> 00:42:21,654
Hey, kid. Hey, you.
Remember me?

449
00:42:21,723 --> 00:42:24,590
- The old guy who looks like you.
- Do I know you?

450
00:42:24,659 --> 00:42:27,093
- Yeah.
- Your voice sounds really familiar.

451
00:42:27,162 --> 00:42:29,722
Here's a clue: I was married
to your mom for about five minutes.

452
00:42:29,798 --> 00:42:32,892
- Really? You sure? 'Cause I don't...
- Yeah. [Chuckles]

453
00:42:32,967 --> 00:42:34,901
[Chattering]

454
00:42:37,405 --> 00:42:40,499
- Well, is he guilty?
- Sir?

455
00:42:40,575 --> 00:42:43,043
Your friend
Colonel Childers.

456
00:42:43,111 --> 00:42:46,342
- Guilty of what, sir?
- Come on, Hayes.

