this has happened before.

538
00:46:51,225 --> 00:46:53,420
We have to be careful here.

539
00:46:53,494 --> 00:46:55,724
This guy is
the warrior's warrior.

540
00:46:55,797 --> 00:47:01,360
A Navy Cross, two Silver Stars
for composure in battle.

541
00:47:01,436 --> 00:47:04,462
He has no wife, no kids,
just the Corps.

542
00:47:04,539 --> 00:47:08,873
He was our best.
Thats why he was sent.

543
00:47:08,943 --> 00:47:11,138
He's not on trial for the
good service he gave the country,

544
00:47:11,212 --> 00:47:13,680
<i>but for what he did</i>
<i>on the wall in Yemen, period.</i>

545
00:47:13,748 --> 00:47:15,648
Major, nobody wants to say it,

546
00:47:15,717 --> 00:47:18,709
but it occurs to me we're trying
to set an example here.

547
00:47:18,786 --> 00:47:21,653
So lets set it and show
the world we mean business.

548
00:47:21,723 --> 00:47:26,126
The first charge supports the death
penalty, and I say we go for it.

549
00:47:26,194 --> 00:47:27,991
No more death.

550
00:47:28,062 --> 00:47:30,758
I'll see that he never gets another
command and I'll put him in jail,

551
00:47:30,832 --> 00:47:34,461
but I will not seek death for a man
who served his country honorably.

552
00:47:34,535 --> 00:47:36,799
<i>I don't want it</i>
<i>brought up again.</i>

553
00:47:36,871 --> 00:47:40,068
We gotta show
Childers' state of mind.

554
00:47:40,141 --> 00:47:42,166
We gotta prove he went out
with intent to kill,

555
00:47:42,243 --> 00:47:44,473
and that is not going to be easy.

556
00:47:44,545 --> 00:47:47,173
Whether a man is charged
with murder or hailed as a hero...

557
00:47:47,248 --> 00:47:49,910
is sometimes a very thin line.

558
00:47:49,984 --> 00:47:54,114
Our case is this: Childers receives
orders that a regularly scheduled,

559
00:47:54,188 --> 00:47:57,851
lawful protest outside
our embassy in Yemen is unruly.

560
00:47:57,925 --> 00:48:00,792
He is to secure
or evacuate the premises.

561
00:48:00,862 --> 00:48:03,626
There has been no violence
prior to his arrival.

562
00:48:03,698 --> 00:48:05,131
Once there, Ambassador Mourain...

563
00:48:05,199 --> 00:48:07,861
does not feel the situation
warrants evacuation.

564
00:48:07,935 --> 00:48:10,301
- Childers ignores him.
- <i>There was sniper fire.</i>

565
00:48:10,371 --> 00:48:13,397
They draw fire from snipers
across the street.

566
00:48:13,474 --> 00:48:17,001
Childers retaliates into an unarmed
crowd in front of the embassy.

567
00:48:17,078 --> 00:48:21,037
A crowd of women and children.
He shot the wrong people.

568
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:25,084
<i>[Man On Radio]</i>
<i>All right, here's what this means.</i>

569
00:48:25,153 --> 00:48:27,678
<i>Murder... Obviously, he could get</i>
<i>up to the death penalty.</i>

570
00:48:27,755 --> 00:48:29,313
<i>Conduct unbecoming an officer.</i>

571
00:48:29,390 --> 00:48:32,154
<i>Max is dismissal</i>
<i>with a dishonorable discharge,</i>

572
00:48:32,226 --> 00:48:36,060
<i>forfeiture of all pay and allowances</i>
<i>and confinement for one year.</i>

573
00:48:36,130 --> 00:48:38,155
<i>[Woman] What about breach</i>
<i>of peace? What is that?</i>

574
00:48:38,232 --> 00:48:40,291
<i>Breaching the peace is minor.</i>

575
00:48:40,368 --> 00:48:43,599
<i>That means participating in an act</i>
<i>of violent or turbulent nature...</i>

576
00:48:43,671 --> 00:48:46,834
<i>that deprives the community of the</i>
<i>peace and tranquility it deserves.</i>

577
00:48:46,908 --> 00:48:50,139
<i>Its sort of the military equivalent</i>
<i>of the civilian misdemeanor.</i>

578
00:48:50,211 --> 00:48:52,645
- <i>No big deal.</i>
- [Chattering, Shouting]

579
00:48:53,948 --> 00:48:57,111
[Man] There he is!
You goddamn baby killer!

580
00:48:57,185 --> 00:48:59,119
<i>Baby killer!</i>

581
00:49:00,588 --> 00:49:02,522
<i>You're disgusting!</i>

582
00:49:02,590 --> 00:49:05,855
I'm not answering any questions,
all right? Get out of here. Go away.

583
00:49:05,927 --> 00:49:09,226
You fucking baby killer!

584
00:49:09,297 --> 00:49:11,561
Fuck you!

585
00:49:13,534 --> 00:49:16,469
Who the fuck are you
to spit on this uniform? Huh?

586
00:49:32,920 --> 00:49:34,785
You ever play blackjack, Colonel?

587
00:49:34,856 --> 00:49:38,121
Not really.

588
00:49:39,560 --> 00:49:43,724
There are no intangibles.
Its all odds, sir.

589
00:49:43,798 --> 00:49:46,790
You know them, you'll beat
the guy next to you.

590
00:49:46,868 --> 00:49:49,268
You know what cards have been
played, you'll beat the house.

591
00:49:51,606 --> 00:49:55,303
Sometimes you just can't win
no matter what you do.

592
00:49:56,944 --> 00:50:00,812
I saw your man on television
knockin' some zit-faced kid around.

593
00:50:00,882 --> 00:50:03,009
You have to understand the kind of
pressure Childers has been under.

594
00:50:03,084 --> 00:50:05,985
A man with that kind of service...
No, no thanks.

595
00:50:06,053 --> 00:50:09,147
This was a rescue mission
that went bad. Nothing more.

596
00:50:09,223 --> 00:50:11,691
You're aware, Colonel,
we could ask for the death penalty.

597
00:50:11,759 --> 00:50:13,192
You're not serious.

598
00:50:13,261 --> 00:50:15,855
Oh, I'm very serious.
In fact, its been suggested.

599
00:50:15,930 --> 00:50:19,331
What do you think would happen
if a Yemeni killed 83 Americans?

600
00:50:19,400 --> 00:50:21,197
He'd have a trial
that would last for one day,

601
00:50:21,269 --> 00:50:22,531
and they'd take off his head.

602
00:50:22,603 --> 00:50:24,537
Have a seat, Colonel.

603
00:50:25,973 --> 00:50:27,907
Please.

604
00:50:33,648 --> 00:50:35,548
So here it is:
You plead him out. Guilty.

605
00:50:35,616 --> 00:50:37,311
He throws himself at the mercy.

606
00:50:37,385 --> 00:50:40,218
- We'll help him out at sentencing.
- How much help?

607
00:50:40,288 --> 00:50:42,813
I'm not about to promise you
anything, but I'd say...

608
00:50:42,890 --> 00:50:45,882
in the neighborhood of ten
to fifteen, out in seven.

609
00:50:45,960 --> 00:50:47,086
Major,

610
00:50:47,161 --> 00:50:50,153
do you know what the life expectancy
was for a second lieutenant...

611
00:50:50,231 --> 00:50:53,496
dropped into a combat zone
in Vietnam in 1968?

612
00:50:53,568 --> 00:50:56,002
I don't have time
for 20 questions, sir.

613
00:50:56,070 --> 00:50:58,732
Then whats all this shit about
the odds of winning at blackjack?

614
00:50:58,806 --> 00:51:03,641
You got time.
Take a guess.

615
00:51:03,711 --> 00:51:07,010
My guess is your man's going down
'cause he deserves to go down.

616
00:51:08,983 --> 00:51:13,420
I got a question for you, Colonel.
What happened at Ca Lu?

617
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:16,923
<i>The battle of Ca Lu,</i>
<i>Vietnam.</i>

618
00:51:16,991 --> 00:51:20,290
You were there with Childers.
Something happened. What was it?

619
00:51:20,361 --> 00:51:24,127
Fuck you is what happened
at Ca Lu, Biggs.

620
00:51:25,199 --> 00:51:27,133
Two weeks.

621
00:51:27,201 --> 00:51:28,634
Life expectancy of
a second lieutenant...

622
00:51:28,703 --> 00:51:31,194
in combat in Vietnam
was two weeks.

623
00:51:31,272 --> 00:51:32,705
Sir, I need more time
to prepare this case.

624
00:51:32,773 --> 00:51:34,968
I need your permission
to go to Yemen...

625
00:51:35,042 --> 00:51:38,637
Its all here, Hodge. We did an
exhaustive Article 32 investigation.

626
00:51:38,713 --> 00:51:41,273
This thing happened
3,000 miles away. I need more time.

627
00:51:41,349 --> 00:51:43,044
Colonel, its all here.

628
00:51:43,117 --> 00:51:45,278
We had it brought from Yemen,
and its not unusual to convene...

629
00:51:45,353 --> 00:51:47,287
a court-martial
on short notice.

630
00:51:47,355 --> 00:51:50,984
There could be witnesses, something
the investigators overlooked, sir.

631
00:51:51,058 --> 00:51:53,993
Don't you think Colonel Childers
is entitled all consideration?

632
00:51:54,061 --> 00:51:57,963
<i>Colonel Hodges, I don't care</i>
<i>if you go to China.</i>

633
00:51:58,032 --> 00:51:59,966
We have our marching orders,
and this court-martial...

634
00:52:00,034 --> 00:52:01,934
will convene
at 0900 a week Monday.

635
00:52:02,003 --> 00:52:05,097
- Now, is that clear?
- Yes, sir.

636
00:52:05,172 --> 00:52:08,505
<i>[Man Leading Cadence,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

637
00:52:08,576 --> 00:52:11,204
<i>[Men]</i>
<i>One! Two!</i>

638
00:52:17,551 --> 00:52:19,485
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

639
00:52:20,921 --> 00:52:25,415
...contact the sergeant?
- He's off-base, sir.

640
00:52:28,129 --> 00:52:30,063
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

641
00:52:35,569 --> 00:52:37,503
Terry?

642
00:52:51,252 --> 00:52:53,186
Terry?

643
00:52:58,993 --> 00:53:00,927
Childers?

644
00:53:06,467 --> 00:53:08,526
Ohh.

645
00:53:08,602 --> 00:53:10,536
<i>Oh, shit.</i>

646
00:53:13,641 --> 00:53:15,905
Its okay.

647
00:53:15,976 --> 00:53:17,910
- <i>[Sighs]</i>
- Its okay.

648
00:53:17,978 --> 00:53:20,242
- I wasn't...
- No, no. I know.

649
00:53:21,615 --> 00:53:25,551
Its okay. Its all right.
I know. Believe me, I know.

650
00:53:27,088 --> 00:53:30,888
[Sighs] Can I leave you alone
with that thing in the house?

651
00:53:30,958 --> 00:53:32,926
Yeah. I ain't goin' six
on you, Hodge.

652
00:53:32,993 --> 00:53:33,925
I'm goin' to Yemen.

653
00:53:33,994 --> 00:53:36,292
If I have to stick your ass
in a hospital till I get back,

654
00:53:36,364 --> 00:53:40,425
- that is what I will do.
