660
00:53:57,151 --> 00:54:01,349
[Sighs] You plead guilty, its
ten to fifteen. You're out in seven.

661
00:54:01,422 --> 00:54:05,290
- What do you think?
- I think they're out to crucify you.

662
00:54:05,359 --> 00:54:09,921
For a whole lot of reasons,
I say we take it and call it a day.

663
00:54:11,298 --> 00:54:13,232
[Sniffles]

664
00:54:21,809 --> 00:54:25,245
I did what they
asked me to do, Hodge.

665
00:54:25,312 --> 00:54:28,679
I lost marines over there.

666
00:54:34,889 --> 00:54:37,551
If I'm guilty of this,

667
00:54:37,625 --> 00:54:42,585
I'm guilty of everything I've done
in combat for the last 30 years.

668
00:54:44,865 --> 00:54:47,231
<i>[Woman Chattering]</i>

669
00:54:47,301 --> 00:54:49,235
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>I don't know.</i>

670
00:55:32,012 --> 00:55:35,209
Colonel Hodges?
Captain Hustings.

671
00:55:35,282 --> 00:55:38,115
I'm not in uniform and I'm not
saluting because of the snipers.

672
00:55:38,185 --> 00:55:40,847
Please know that I'm saluting
on the inside.

673
00:55:40,921 --> 00:55:43,355
I've got some Kevlar back there
with your name on it.

674
00:55:43,424 --> 00:55:46,154
We're not the most popular team
in town right now, sir.

675
00:55:46,227 --> 00:55:48,024
Hustings, are you a wiseass?

676
00:55:48,095 --> 00:55:50,962
My mother prefers to
think of me as glib, sir.

677
00:55:51,031 --> 00:55:56,094
Very well then. You will most glibly
belay all bullshit and drive on.

678
00:55:56,170 --> 00:55:58,638
Roger that, sir.

679
00:56:20,027 --> 00:56:23,690
